review_blob: Pitch black, small tan head. Aroma is a heavy smoky, wood. Full bodied and malty, taste of chocolate, smoked meat on the finish. Not very bitter for an imperial stout, and the mouthfeel is fantastic. If you like them dark and smokey pick this up.

Pretty average as far as pumpkin beers go. Didnt get much of the cranberry except a little tart on the aftertaste. Easy to drink, will definetly purchase later in the season to compare when more Pumpkin beers are out.
Smells nice, tastes good. Clove, spice, mouthfeel is a bit thin for my taste. Not a fantastic pumpkin but for the price is great.
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Brown with big frothy head. Roasted malts and caramel with brown sugar. Creamy and delicious, would purchase again.
Light ambergold, small off white head. Malty alcohol, caramel with a light body. Decent, but not good enough to tempt me to buy it again.
Bottle to snifter. Clear dark brown/red. Very malty caramel. Very sweet, with alcohol. Dry, hoppy finish. Good choice if youre a dopplebock fan, but there are better, cheaper ones out there.

Bottle to snifter. Pours dark black, decent off-white head. Malty, honey and caramel. Heavy and sweet, full bodied with a creamy, oily texture. 

Delicious, maybe a little heavy for me. Would purchase again.
Bottle to snifter. Pours deep brown with a small, dark, head. Lots of malt, all the character you would expect from a great dopplebock
Snifter. Dark reddish brown, medium head. Smells of spices and caramel, roasted malt. Very sweet with a bit of alcohol. Fantastic beer, would purchase again.

Pours Dark amber brown, small head. Dark sweet maple & carmel aroma. Taste is malt and caramel, some chocolate/toffee. 

Probably one of the best dopplebocks Ive had. Will be purchasing this again.

A good dark, malty beer. Not much head, pours a dark chocolate brown. Caramely, not as big of flavor as I expected, but extremely delicious.

Will buy this again.

Bottle/Snifter.

A very funky brew. Pours burnt golden orange with a big head. Aroma of heavy grassy hops, a tinge of something unpleasant, not sure how to describe it.  A bitter, slightly sour taste, reminiscent of brown rice.

This particular bottle was not stored under best conditions, but this is still a very, very unique/funky beer. An interesting try, but I would not buy again.

Aroma: Caramel.
Apperance: No head, deep rust. Particles on bottom.
Taste: Bitter and sour, , tangy aftertaste.
Palate: Medium bodied, no carbonation.

A weird, weird beer. Worth a try but I wouldnt buy it again.
